==English==
===Etymology===
{{I.}} ''lava'', lava, originally, in [[Naples]], a [[torrent]] of [[rain]] overflowing the streets, from Italian and {{L.}} ''[[lavare]]'', to wash. See '''[[lave]]'''

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|läʹvə}}, {{IPA|/lɑːvə/}}, {{SAMPA|/lA:v@/}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːvə|-ɑːvə]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The melted [[rock]] ejected by a [[volcano]] from its [[crater]] or [[fissure]]d sides.<!--encyclopedic info: It flows out in streams sometimes miles or kilometres in length. It also issues from fissures in the earth's surface, and forms beds covering many square miles, as in the Northwestern United States.
#: '''Note:''' Lavas are classed, according to their 1) structure, as [[scoriaceous]] or [[cellular]], [[glassy]], [[stony]], etc., 2) according to the material of which they consist, as [[doleritic]], [[trachytic]], etc., and 3) according to their form in flows as either [[aa]] or [[pahoehoe]].-->
# [[magma]]<!--, molten rock ''within'' the earth.-->

